  "page_number": 2,
  "context": "2 institution but in no case shall exceed 24 units per semester or term (CMO 40, s.2008; CM0 30, s.2009).\n\nSection 5 Any teaching load in excess of the normal or regular teaching load shall be considered as overload. Overload partakes of the nature of temporary extra assignment and compensation therefore shall be considered as an overload honorarium if within the 8-hour work period and does not form part of the regular or basic pay.\n\nOverload performed beyond the eight-hour daily work is overtime work (CMO 40, s.2008; CMO 30, s.2009).\n\nSection 6 Honoraria may be paid to teaching personnel engaged in actual classroom teaching, whose teaching load is outside of the regular office hours or in excess of the regular load (Sec.63 (a) General Provisions of RA 11975).\n\nSection 7 Government employees whose regular schedule of work falls between 6 a.m. and 6 p.m., including those under the flexible work arrangements whose nature of services requires their rendition within the same period are excluded from the grant of Night Shift Differential Pay. The services they rendered beyond the regular eight (8)-hour work schedules shall be compensated in accordance with the existing laws, rules, and regulations on overtime services and overtime pay (CSC-DBM-GCGOCCs Joint Circular No. 1, s.2023).\n\n7.1 An employee whose prescribed work schedule is from 8 a.m. to 5 p.m., but renders services until 7 p.m., as authorized by the head of agency. The hours worked from 6 p.m. to 7 p.m. shall not be covered by Night Shift Differential Pay, but shall be compensated in accordance with the rules and regulations on overtime services and overtime pay.\n\n7.2 An employee whose agency implements compressed workweek with ten (10) working hours for four days in a week, has the prescribed work schedule from 8 a.m. to 7 p.m., with 12 p.m. to 1 p.m. as the time for lunch. The hours worked from 6 p.m. to 7 p.m. shall not be covered by Night Shift Differential Pay. In case the employee renders services beyond the prescribed ten (10) hours of work, as authorized by the head of agency, he/she shall be compensated in accordance with the rules and regulations on overtime services and overtime pay.",
  "qa_pairs": [
    {
      "question": "What is the maximum teaching load allowed per semester or term?",
      "answer": "24 units."
    },
    {
      "question": "Can teaching load exceed the normal or regular teaching load?",
      "answer": "Yes, it can be considered as overload."
    },
    {
      "question": "What is considered overtime work in teaching?",
      "answer": "Any teaching load beyond the eight-hour daily work period."
    },
    {
      "question": "Are honoraria paid to teaching personnel for actual classroom teaching?",
      "answer": "Yes, if their teaching load is outside of regular office hours or in excess of regular load."
    },
    {
      "question": "What are excluded from Night Shift Differential Pay?",
      "answer": "Government employees whose regular schedule of work falls between 6 a.m. and 6 p.m."
    },
    {
      "question": "Can an employee render services beyond the prescribed work schedule?",
      "answer": "Yes, but it will not be covered by Night Shift Differential Pay."
    },
    {
      "question": "What happens if an employee renders services beyond the prescribed ten hours of work?",
      "answer": "They shall be compensated in accordance with the rules and regulations on overtime services and overtime pay."
    },
    {
      "question": "What is the compressed workweek implemented by some agencies?",
      "answer": "Ten working hours for four days in a week."
    },
    {
      "question": "What is the prescribed work schedule of an employee implementing compressed workweek?",
      "answer": "From 8 a.m. to 7 p.m., with 12 p.m. to 1 p.m. as the time for lunch."
    },
    {
      "question": "Are there any strict constraints in rendering services beyond the prescribed schedule?",
      "answer": "Yes, an employee shall be compensated in accordance with the rules and regulations on overtime services and overtime pay."
    },
    {
      "question": "Can an employee render services beyond the prescribed work schedule without authorization from the head of agency?",
      "answer": "No."
    },
    {
      "question": "What is the purpose of Night Shift Differential Pay?",
      "answer": "To compensate government employees for rendering services beyond the regular eight-hour work schedules."
    },
    {
      "question": "Are there any exceptions to the rule on Night Shift Differential Pay?",
      "answer": "Yes, government employees whose regular schedule of work falls between 6 a.m. and 6 p.m. are excluded from the grant of Night Shift Differential Pay."
    },
    {
      "question": "Can an employee render services beyond the prescribed work schedule without any additional compensation?",
      "answer": "Yes, if authorized by the head of agency."
    },
    {
      "question": "What is the maximum teaching load allowed per semester or term for employees under CMO 40 and CMO 30?",
      "answer": "24 units."
    },
    {
      "question": "What is the purpose of CMO 40 and CMO 30?",
      "answer": "To regulate the teaching load and overload in government schools and institutions."
    },
    {
      "question": "Are there any consequences for exceeding the maximum teaching load allowed per semester or term?",
      "answer": "Yes, it can be considered as overload and shall be compensated accordingly."
    },
    {
      "question": "What is the nature of services rendered by employees whose regular schedule of work falls between 6 a.m. and 6 p.m.?",
      "answer": "Temporary extra assignment."
    },
    {
      "question": "Are there any exceptions to the rule on Night Shift Differential Pay for government employees?",
      "answer": "Yes, those whose regular schedule of work falls between 6 a.m. and 6 p.m. are excluded from the grant of Night Shift Differential Pay."
